						<summary>

						<p>A pillar within the same temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vikrama-chōḷadēva: Year 22 = 1276-77 A.D. (?)</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records that the pillar, on which the epigraph is inscribed, was the gift of a certain Mōḍan Tirunaṭṭapperumāḷ, a <hi rend="italic">Śāliya</hi> of the village of Śōḻamādēvi.</p>						

